{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1080,"text":"Space, the final frontier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":5880,"text":"I first heard these words\nwhen I was just six years old,"},{"time":9360,"text":"and I was completely inspired."},{"time":11640,"text":"I wanted to explore strange new worlds."},{"time":14040,"text":"I wanted to seek out new life."},{"time":15560,"text":"I wanted to see everything\nthat the universe had to offer."},{"time":19840,"text":"And those dreams, those words,\nthey took me on a journey,"},{"time":23560,"text":"a journey of discovery,"},{"time":25040,"text":"through school, through university,"},{"time":27240,"text":"to do a PhD and finally\nto become a professional astronomer."},{"time":31920,"text":"Now, I learned two amazing things,"},{"time":34960,"text":"one slightly unfortunate,"},{"time":36520,"text":"when I was doing my PhD."},{"time":38600,"text":"I learned that the reality was"},{"time":41040,"text":"I wouldn't be piloting\na starship anytime soon."},{"time":45440,"text":"But I also learned that the universe\nis strange, wonderful and vast,"},{"time":50080,"text":"actually too vast\nto be explored by spaceship."},{"time":53720,"text":"And so I turned my attention\nto astronomy, to using telescopes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57840,"text":"Now, I show you before you\nan image of the night sky."},{"time":60640,"text":"You might see it anywhere in the world."},{"time":63040,"text":"And all of these stars are part\nof our local galaxy, the Milky Way."},{"time":67560,"text":"Now, if you were to go\nto a darker part of the sky,"},{"time":70280,"text":"a nice dark site, perhaps in the desert,"},{"time":72840,"text":"you might see the center\nof our Milky Way galaxy"},{"time":75280,"text":"spread out before you,\nhundreds of billions of stars."},{"time":78840,"text":"And it's a very beautiful image."},{"time":80440,"text":"It's colorful."},{"time":81800,"text":"And again, this is just\na local corner of our universe."},{"time":85440,"text":"You can see there's\na sort of strange dark dust across it."},{"time":88760,"text":"Now, that is local dust"},{"time":90760,"text":"that's obscuring the light of the stars."},{"time":93440,"text":"But we can do a pretty good job."},{"time":95040,"text":"Just with our own eyes, we can explore\nour little corner of the universe."},{"time":98520,"text":"It's possible to do better."},{"time":99880,"text":"You can use wonderful telescopes\nlike the Hubble Space Telescope."},{"time":104200,"text":"Now, astronomers\nhave put together this image."},{"time":106400,"text":"It's called the Hubble Deep Field,"},{"time":108320,"text":"and they've spent hundreds of hours\nobserving just a tiny patch of the sky"},{"time":112680,"text":"no larger than your thumbnail\nheld at arm's length."},{"time":115520,"text":"And in this image"},{"time":116800,"text":"you can see thousands of galaxies,"},{"time":118480,"text":"and we know that there must be\nhundreds of millions, billions of galaxies"},{"time":121960,"text":"in the entire universe,"},{"time":123360,"text":"some like our own and some very different."},{"time":126040,"text":"So you think, OK, well,\nI can continue this journey."},{"time":128720,"text":"This is easy. I can just\nuse a very powerful telescope"},{"time":131440,"text":"and just look at the sky, no problem."},{"time":133960,"text":"It's actually really missing out\nif we just do that."},{"time":138000,"text":"Now, that's because\neverything I've talked about so far"},{"time":140760,"text":"is just using the visible spectrum,\njust the thing that your eyes can see,"},{"time":144680,"text":"and that's a tiny slice,"},{"time":146120,"text":"a tiny, tiny slice\nof what the universe has to offer us."},{"time":150160,"text":"Now, there's also two very important\nproblems with using visible light."},{"time":154920,"text":"Not only are we missing out\non all the other processes"},{"time":157680,"text":"that are emitting other kinds of light,"},{"time":160880,"text":"but there's two issues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162320,"text":"Now, the first is that dust\nthat I mentioned earlier."},{"time":165720,"text":"The dust stops the visible light\nfrom getting to us."},{"time":168680,"text":"So as we look deeper\ninto the universe, we see less light."},{"time":173400,"text":"The dust stops it getting to us."},{"time":175520,"text":"But there's a really strange problem\nwith using visible light"},{"time":178960,"text":"in order to try and explore the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181640,"text":"Now take a break for a minute."},{"time":183920,"text":"Say you're standing on a corner,\na busy street corner."},{"time":187080,"text":"There's cars going by."},{"time":188600,"text":"An ambulance approaches."},{"time":190840,"text":"It has a high-pitched siren."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192240,"text":"(Imitates a siren passing by)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":196000,"text":"The siren appeared to change in pitch"},{"time":198360,"text":"as it moved towards and away from you."},{"time":200960,"text":"The ambulance driver did not change\nthe siren just to mess with you."},{"time":206040,"text":"That was a product of your perception."},{"time":208640,"text":"The sound waves,\nas the ambulance approached,"},{"time":211400,"text":"were compressed,"},{"time":212640,"text":"and they changed higher in pitch."},{"time":214600,"text":"As the ambulance receded,\nthe sound waves were stretched,"},{"time":217400,"text":"and they sounded lower in pitch."},{"time":219480,"text":"The same thing happens with light."},{"time":222040,"text":"Objects moving towards us,"},{"time":224440,"text":"their light waves are compressed\nand they appear bluer."},{"time":227640,"text":"Objects moving away from us,"},{"time":229880,"text":"their light waves are stretched,\nand they appear redder."},{"time":232560,"text":"So we call these effects\nblueshift and redshift."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236440,"text":"Now, our universe is expanding,"},{"time":239400,"text":"so everything is moving away\nfrom everything else,"},{"time":243600,"text":"and that means\neverything appears to be red."},{"time":247040,"text":"And oddly enough, as you look\nmore deeply into the universe,"},{"time":250800,"text":"more distant objects\nare moving away further and faster,"},{"time":255120,"text":"so they appear more red."},{"time":257560,"text":"So if I come back to the Hubble Deep Field"},{"time":260519,"text":"and we were to continue\nto peer deeply into the universe"},{"time":263240,"text":"just using the Hubble,"},{"time":264800,"text":"as we get to a certain distance away,"},{"time":267520,"text":"everything becomes red,"},{"time":269920,"text":"and that presents something of a problem."},{"time":271920,"text":"Eventually, we get so far away"},{"time":274000,"text":"everything is shifted into the infrared"},{"time":277000,"text":"and we can't see anything at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279680,"text":"So there must be a way around this."},{"time":281400,"text":"Otherwise, I'm limited in my journey."},{"time":283240,"text":"I wanted to explore the whole universe,"},{"time":285160,"text":"not just whatever I can see,\nyou know, before the redshift kicks in."},{"time":290160,"text":"There is a technique."},{"time":291440,"text":"It's called radio astronomy."},{"time":292840,"text":"Astronomers have been\nusing this for decades."},{"time":295200,"text":"It's a fantastic technique."},{"time":296520,"text":"I show you the Parkes Radio Telescope,\naffectionately known as \"The Dish.\""},{"time":300040,"text":"You may have seen the movie."},{"time":301840,"text":"And radio is really brilliant."},{"time":303440,"text":"It allows us to peer much more deeply."},{"time":306000,"text":"It doesn't get stopped by dust,"},{"time":308720,"text":"so you can see everything in the universe,"},{"time":311000,"text":"and redshift is less of a problem"},{"time":312880,"text":"because we can build receivers\nthat receive across a large band."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316600,"text":"So what does Parkes see when we turn it\nto the center of the Milky Way?"},{"time":320560,"text":"We should see something fantastic, right?"},{"time":323160,"text":"Well, we do see something interesting."},{"time":326080,"text":"All that dust has gone."},{"time":327760,"text":"As I mentioned, radio goes\nstraight through dust, so not a problem."},{"time":331840,"text":"But the view is very different."},{"time":333760,"text":"We can see that the center\nof the Milky Way is aglow,"},{"time":337600,"text":"and this isn't starlight."},{"time":339960,"text":"This is a light called\nsynchrotron radiation,"},{"time":343120,"text":"and it's formed from electrons\nspiraling around cosmic magnetic fields."},{"time":348280,"text":"So the plane is aglow with this light."},{"time":351400,"text":"And we can also see\nstrange tufts coming off of it,"},{"time":354720,"text":"and objects which don't appear to line up"},{"time":357240,"text":"with anything that we can see\nwith our own eyes."},{"time":360520,"text":"But it's hard to really\ninterpret this image,"},{"time":362680,"text":"because as you can see,\nit's very low resolution."},{"time":365480,"text":"Radio waves have a wavelength that's long,"},{"time":367680,"text":"and that makes their resolution poorer."},{"time":370000,"text":"This image is also black and white,"},{"time":372080,"text":"so we don't really know\nwhat is the color of everything in here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376640,"text":"Well, fast-forward to today."},{"time":378040,"text":"We can build telescopes"},{"time":379520,"text":"which can get over these problems."},{"time":382160,"text":"Now, I'm showing you here an image\nof the Murchison Radio Observatory,"},{"time":385520,"text":"a fantastic place\nto build radio telescopes."},{"time":388320,"text":"It's flat, it's dry,"},{"time":390640,"text":"and most importantly, it's radio quiet:"},{"time":393640,"text":"no mobile phones, no Wi-Fi, nothing,"},{"time":396760,"text":"just very, very radio quiet,"},{"time":399280,"text":"so a perfect place\nto build a radio telescope."},{"time":402880,"text":"Now, the telescope that I've been\nworking on for a few years"},{"time":405760,"text":"is called the Murchison Widefield Array,"},{"time":407720,"text":"and I'm going to show you\na little time lapse of it being built."},{"time":410760,"text":"This is a group of undergraduate\nand postgraduate students"},{"time":414040,"text":"located in Perth."},{"time":415320,"text":"We call them the Student Army,"},{"time":417080,"text":"and they volunteered their time\nto build a radio telescope."},{"time":419920,"text":"There's no course credit for this."},{"time":422320,"text":"And they're putting together\nthese radio dipoles."},{"time":425240,"text":"They just receive at low frequencies,\na bit like your FM radio or your TV."},{"time":431000,"text":"And here we are deploying them\nacross the desert."},{"time":434120,"text":"The final telescope\ncovers 10 square kilometers"},{"time":436560,"text":"of the Western Australian desert."},{"time":438720,"text":"And the interesting thing is,\nthere's no moving parts."},{"time":441720,"text":"We just deploy these little antennas"},{"time":444000,"text":"essentially on chicken mesh."},{"time":445880,"text":"It's fairly cheap."},{"time":447320,"text":"Cables take the signals"},{"time":449320,"text":"from the antennas"},{"time":451400,"text":"and bring them\nto central processing units."},{"time":453960,"text":"And it's the size of this telescope,"},{"time":455760,"text":"the fact that we've built it\nover the entire desert"},{"time":458440,"text":"that gives us a better\nresolution than Parkes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461880,"text":"Now, eventually all those cables\nbring them to a unit"},{"time":465440,"text":"which sends it off\nto a supercomputer here in Perth,"},{"time":469000,"text":"and that's where I come in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471320,"text":"(Sighs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":472560,"text":"Radio data."},{"time":473800,"text":"I have spent the last five years"},{"time":475640,"text":"working with very difficult,\nvery interesting data"},{"time":478520,"text":"that no one had really looked at before."},{"time":480520,"text":"I've spent a long time calibrating it,"},{"time":482680,"text":"running millions of CPU hours\non supercomputers"},{"time":486600,"text":"and really trying to understand that data."},{"time":489360,"text":"And with this telescope,"},{"time":491320,"text":"with this data,"},{"time":492600,"text":"we've performed a survey\nof the entire southern sky,"},{"time":496560,"text":"the GaLactic and Extragalactic\nAll-sky MWA Survey,"},{"time":501680,"text":"or GLEAM, as I call it."},{"time":504440,"text":"And I'm very excited."},{"time":505920,"text":"This survey is just about to be published,\nbut it hasn't been shown yet,"},{"time":509325,"text":"so you are literally the first people"},{"time":511280,"text":"to see this southern survey\nof the entire sky."},{"time":514799,"text":"So I'm delighted to share with you\nsome images from this survey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518880,"text":"Now, imagine you went to the Murchison,"},{"time":520799,"text":"you camped out underneath the stars"},{"time":522919,"text":"and you looked towards the south."},{"time":524560,"text":"You saw the south's celestial pole,"},{"time":526251,"text":"the galaxy rising."},{"time":527480,"text":"If I fade in the radio light,"},{"time":530120,"text":"this is what we observe with our survey."},{"time":532800,"text":"You can see that the galactic plane\nis no longer dark with dust."},{"time":535880,"text":"It's alight with synchrotron radiation,"},{"time":538320,"text":"and thousands of dots are in the sky."},{"time":540840,"text":"Our large Magellanic Cloud,\nour nearest galactic neighbor,"},{"time":544160,"text":"is orange instead\nof its more familiar blue-white."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547400,"text":"So there's a lot going on in this.\nLet's take a closer look."},{"time":550800,"text":"If we look back\ntowards the galactic center,"},{"time":553240,"text":"where we originally saw the Parkes image\nthat I showed you earlier,"},{"time":556480,"text":"low resolution, black and white,"},{"time":558880,"text":"and we fade to the GLEAM view,"},{"time":562200,"text":"you can see the resolution\nhas gone up by a factor of a hundred."},{"time":566080,"text":"We now have a color view of the sky,"},{"time":568960,"text":"a technicolor view."},{"time":570320,"text":"Now, it's not a false color view."},{"time":573320,"text":"These are real radio colors."},{"time":576600,"text":"What I've done is I've colored\nthe lowest frequencies red"},{"time":579440,"text":"and the highest frequencies blue,"},{"time":581080,"text":"and the middle ones green."},{"time":582680,"text":"And that gives us this rainbow view."},{"time":584920,"text":"And this isn't just false color."},{"time":587200,"text":"The colors in this image\ntell us about the physical processes"},{"time":590160,"text":"going on in the universe."},{"time":591974,"text":"So for instance, if you look\nalong the plane of the galaxy,"},{"time":594760,"text":"it's alight with synchrotron,"},{"time":596240,"text":"which is mostly reddish orange,"},{"time":598640,"text":"but if we look very closely,\nwe see little blue dots."},{"time":602320,"text":"Now, if we zoom in,"},{"time":603920,"text":"these blue dots are ionized plasma"},{"time":606480,"text":"around very bright stars,"},{"time":608680,"text":"and what happens\nis that they block the red light,"},{"time":611480,"text":"so they appear blue."},{"time":613880,"text":"And these can tell us\nabout these star-forming regions"},{"time":616840,"text":"in our galaxy."},{"time":618120,"text":"And we just see them immediately."},{"time":619760,"text":"We look at the galaxy,\nand the color tells us that they're there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622840,"text":"You can see little soap bubbles,"},{"time":624440,"text":"little circular images\naround the galactic plane,"},{"time":627880,"text":"and these are supernova remnants."},{"time":630600,"text":"When a star explodes,"},{"time":632320,"text":"its outer shell is cast off"},{"time":634800,"text":"and it travels outward into space\ngathering up material,"},{"time":638120,"text":"and it produces a little shell."},{"time":640800,"text":"It's been a long-standing\nmystery to astronomers"},{"time":644200,"text":"where all the supernova remnants are."},{"time":646960,"text":"We know that there must be a lot\nof high-energy electrons in the plane"},{"time":651320,"text":"to produce the synchrotron\nradiation that we see,"},{"time":654000,"text":"and we think they're produced\nby supernova remnants,"},{"time":656600,"text":"but there don't seem to be enough."},{"time":658400,"text":"Fortunately, GLEAM is really, really\ngood at detecting supernova remnants,"},{"time":662320,"text":"so we're hoping to have\na new paper out on that soon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665800,"text":"Now, that's fine."},{"time":667080,"text":"We've explored our little local universe,"},{"time":669440,"text":"but I wanted to go deeper,\nI wanted to go further."},{"time":671840,"text":"I wanted to go beyond the Milky Way."},{"time":674520,"text":"Well, as it happens, we can see a very\ninteresting object in the top right,"},{"time":678320,"text":"and this is a local radio galaxy,"},{"time":680560,"text":"Centaurus A."},{"time":682240,"text":"If we zoom in on this,"},{"time":683520,"text":"we can see that there are\ntwo huge plumes going out into space."},{"time":687600,"text":"And if you look right in the center\nbetween those two plumes,"},{"time":690520,"text":"you'll see a galaxy just like our own."},{"time":692920,"text":"It's a spiral. It has a dust lane."},{"time":695400,"text":"It's a normal galaxy."},{"time":697040,"text":"But these jets\nare only visible in the radio."},{"time":700680,"text":"If we looked in the visible,\nwe wouldn't even know they were there,"},{"time":703880,"text":"and they're thousands of times larger\nthan the host galaxy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707480,"text":"What's going on?\nWhat's producing these jets?"},{"time":711160,"text":"At the center of every galaxy\nthat we know about"},{"time":714720,"text":"is a supermassive black hole."},{"time":717000,"text":"Now, black holes are invisible.\nThat's why they're called that."},{"time":720440,"text":"All you can see is the deflection\nof the light around them,"},{"time":723480,"text":"and occasionally, when a star\nor a cloud of gas comes into their orbit,"},{"time":727800,"text":"it is ripped apart by tidal forces,"},{"time":730560,"text":"forming what we call an accretion disk."},{"time":733640,"text":"The accretion disk\nglows brightly in the x-rays,"},{"time":736880,"text":"and huge magnetic fields\ncan launch the material into space"},{"time":741320,"text":"at nearly the speed of light."},{"time":743520,"text":"So these jets are visible in the radio"},{"time":747240,"text":"and this is what we pick up in our survey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750040,"text":"Well, very well, so we've seen\none radio galaxy. That's nice."},{"time":754080,"text":"But if you just look\nat the top of that image,"},{"time":756280,"text":"you'll see another radio galaxy."},{"time":758040,"text":"It's a little bit smaller,\nand that's just because it's further away."},{"time":761800,"text":"OK. Two radio galaxies."},{"time":764480,"text":"We can see this. This is fine."},{"time":766080,"text":"Well, what about all the other dots?"},{"time":767840,"text":"Presumably those are just stars."},{"time":769880,"text":"They're not."},{"time":771120,"text":"They're all radio galaxies."},{"time":773320,"text":"Every single one of the dots in this image"},{"time":776240,"text":"is a distant galaxy,"},{"time":778000,"text":"millions to billions of light-years away"},{"time":780880,"text":"with a supermassive\nblack hole at its center"},{"time":783520,"text":"pushing material into space\nat nearly the speed of light."},{"time":787120,"text":"It is mind-blowing."},{"time":789680,"text":"And this survey is even larger\nthan what I've shown here."},{"time":793440,"text":"If we zoom out to\nthe full extent of the survey,"},{"time":796000,"text":"you can see I found 300,000\nof these radio galaxies."},{"time":800120,"text":"So it's truly an epic journey."},{"time":803040,"text":"We've discovered all of these galaxies"},{"time":805720,"text":"right back to the very first\nsupermassive black holes."},{"time":809960,"text":"I'm very proud of this,\nand it will be published next week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813280,"text":"Now, that's not all."},{"time":816120,"text":"I've explored the furthest reaches\nof the galaxy with this survey,"},{"time":820480,"text":"but there's something\neven more in this image."},{"time":824320,"text":"Now, I'll take you right back\nto the dawn of time."},{"time":827640,"text":"When the universe formed,\nit was a big bang,"},{"time":831320,"text":"which left the universe\nas a sea of hydrogen,"},{"time":835400,"text":"neutral hydrogen."},{"time":836920,"text":"And when the very first stars\nand galaxies switched on,"},{"time":839720,"text":"they ionized that hydrogen."},{"time":841840,"text":"So the universe went\nfrom neutral to ionized."},{"time":846160,"text":"That imprinted a signal all around us."},{"time":849360,"text":"Everywhere, it pervades us,"},{"time":851120,"text":"like the Force."},{"time":852560,"text":"Now, because that happened so long ago,"},{"time":857000,"text":"the signal was redshifted,"},{"time":859560,"text":"so now that signal\nis at very low frequencies."},{"time":862880,"text":"It's at the same frequency as my survey,"},{"time":865360,"text":"but it's so faint."},{"time":866760,"text":"It's a billionth the size\nof any of the objects in my survey."},{"time":871320,"text":"So our telescope may not be quite\nsensitive enough to pick up this signal."},{"time":876240,"text":"However, there's a new radio telescope."},{"time":878760,"text":"So I can't have a starship,"},{"time":880440,"text":"but I can hopefully have"},{"time":881720,"text":"one of the biggest\nradio telescopes in the world."},{"time":884600,"text":"We're building the Square Kilometre Array,\na new radio telescope,"},{"time":888240,"text":"and it's going to be a thousand\ntimes bigger than the MWA,"},{"time":891000,"text":"a thousand times more sensitive,\nand have an even better resolution."},{"time":894240,"text":"So we should find\ntens of millions of galaxies."},{"time":896480,"text":"And perhaps, deep in that signal,"},{"time":898840,"text":"I will get to look upon the very first\nstars and galaxies switching on,"},{"time":903040,"text":"the beginning of time itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905920,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":907160,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}